import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='group_size', kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['group_size'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['group_size'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['group_size'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['group_size'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of group sizes?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Group Size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.countplot(x="group_type", data=data, palette="Set2")
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    chart.axhline(y=data['group_type'].value_counts().max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['group_type'].value_counts().max()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

data = pd.read_csv('lookup_groups.csv')
chart = plot(data)
plt.title('What is the most common group type?', wrap=True)
plt.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load data
data = pd.read_csv('lookup_groups.csv')

# Convert date fields to date types
data['date_joined'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date_joined'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')

# Drop rows with NaT values
data = data[pd.notna(data['date_joined'])]

# Create box plot
sns.boxplot(x=data['age'])

# Add title and labels
plt.title('What is the average age of group members?')
plt.xlabel('Age')

# Add median line
median = data['age'].median()
plt.axvline(median, color='red', label=f'Median: {median:.2f}')

# Add legend
plt.legend()

# Show plot
plt.show()
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gender_counts = data['gender'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(gender_counts, labels=gender_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=90, colors=['#ff9999','#66b3ff'])
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of group members?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Gender', loc='center left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0, 0.5, 1))
    return plt

data = pd.read_csv('lookup_groups.csv')
chart = plot(data)
```
